  {% endfor %}
</Accordion>

## Real-time events

`subscribe()` returns a `TypedEventStream<MessageEvent>`. Pass an event type string to narrow the type automatically.

```ts
// All message events
for await (const event of im.messages.subscribe()) {
  event.type; // "message.sent" | "message.received" | "message.updated" | "message.sendError"
}

// Only incoming messages - TS knows the exact shape
for await (const event of im.messages.subscribe("message.received")) {
  console.log(event.message.text);
  console.log(event.chatGuid);
}
```

{% set messageEvent = symbol("ts:@photon-ai/advanced-imessage#MessageEvent") %}
<Accordion title="Message event types" description="{{ messageEvent.doc.summary }}">
  | `event.{{ messageEvent.discriminator }}` | Extra fields |
  |---|---|
  {% for v in messageEvent.variants -%}
  | `{{ v.name }}` | {% if v.fields and v.fields|length %}{% for f in v.fields %}`{{ f.name }}{% if f.optional %}?{% endif %}`{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% else %}-{% endif %} |
  {% endfor %}
</Accordion>

### Stream operators

`TypedEventStream` supports `.filter()`, `.map()`, and `.take()`:

```ts
const incoming = im.messages
  .subscribe("message.received")
  .filter((e) => e.message.text !== undefined)
  .map((e) => ({ from: e.message.sender?.address, text: e.message.text! }));

for await (const { from, text } of incoming) {
  console.log(`[${from}] ${text}`);
}
```

Streams implement `Symbol.asyncDispose`:

```ts
await using stream = im.messages.subscribe("message.received");
for await (const event of stream) {
  ...
}
```

## Stream catch-up

When a stream disconnects, messages keep arriving on the server. Every stream event includes an opaque `cursor` string you can persist. On reconnect, use `fetchMissed()` to replay everything you missed, then resume the live stream.

```ts
let cursor = loadPersistedCursor(); // your storage

// 1. Catch up on anything missed while disconnected
if (cursor) {
  for await (const msg of im.messages.fetchMissed(cursor)) {
    processMissedMessage(msg);
  }
}

// 2. Resume live stream, tracking cursor for next time
for await (const event of im.messages.subscribe()) {
  if (event.cursor) cursor = event.cursor;
  processEvent(event);
}

// 3. Persist cursor when done (or periodically)
persistCursor(cursor);
```

`fetchMissed(cursor)` returns `Paginated<Message>` — the same auto-pagination as `list()`. Results are ordered chronologically so they can be replayed in order.

**`FetchMissedOptions`**

| Option | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `chatGuid` | `ChatGuid` | Restrict to messages in a specific chat |
| `limit` | `number` | Maximum number of messages per page |

```ts
im.messages.fetchMissed(cursor!, { chatGuid: chat, limit: 100 });
```

The cursor is opaque — treat it as a string, persist it, and pass it back. The server handles the rest.

## Miscellaneous

```ts
// Acknowledge a silenced message notification
await im.messages.notifySilenced(chat, messageGuid);

// Extract embedded media from a rich message (link preview images, etc.)
const items = await im.messages.getEmbeddedMedia(chat, messageGuid);
// items: Array<{ data: Uint8Array; mimeType: string }>
```
